<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This is a fish-parasitic copepod, living in the gill cavity of the host. Known hosts of this copepod are the gobiid fishes 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Temminck &amp; Schlegel" baseAuthorityYear="1845" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Acanthogobius" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Acanthogobius flavimanus" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="flavimanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Acanthogobius flavimanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Temminck &amp; Schlegel, 1845) and 
<taxonomicName class="Hexanauplia" genus="A." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. hasta" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hasta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A. hasta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Temminck &amp; Schlegel, 1845).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
